e to 16,000,000 peoplecould visit the region during July-September.\", \"from\": 1971, \"to\": 2142, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2035, \"end\": 2040, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.090223790884818e-27, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"travel\", \"from\": 1976, \"to\": 1982}, {\"ngram\": \"one reason\", \"from\": 1989, \"to\": 1999}, {\"ngram\": \"the rise\", \"from\": 2004, \"to\": 2012}, {\"ngram\": \"the blood-suckers\", \"from\": 2016, \"to\": 2033}, {\"ngram\": \"the region\", \"from\": 2109, \"to\": 2119}, {\"ngram\": \"July-September\", \"from\": 2127, \"to\": 2141}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ask any swimmer what they'd prefer to swim in, clean water or a river riddled with 'faecal matter', we can take a guess which they'd prefer.\", \"from\": 2144, \"to\": 2284, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"any swimmer\", \"from\": 2148, \"to\": 2159}, {\"ngram\": \"clean water\", \"from\": 2191, \"to\": 2202}, {\"ngram\": \"a river\", \"from\": 2206, \"to\": 2213}, {\"ngram\": \"faecal matter\", \"from\": 2228, \"to\": 2241}, {\"ngram\": \"a guess\", \"from\": 2256, \"to\": 2263}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But this is the question facing Olympic athletes dreaming of taking home the gold in sports such as marathon swimming or triathlon in only two weeks.\", \"from\": 2286, \"to\": 2435, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the question\", \"from\": 2298, \"to\": 2310}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic athletes\", \"from\": 2318, \"to\": 2334}, {\"ngram\": \"the gold\", \"from\": 2359, \"to\": 2367}, {\"ngram\": \"sports\", \"from\": 2371, \"to\": 2377}, {\"ngram\": \"marathon swimming\", \"from\": 2386, \"to\": 2403}, {\"ngram\": \"triathlon\", \"from\": 2407, \"to\": 2416}, {\"ngram\": \"only two weeks\", \"from\": 2420, \"to\": 2434}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If everything goes to plan, athletes will take a dip in the Seine - the river that has been illegal to swim in for a century due to high pollution levels.\", \"from\": 2437, \"to\": 2591, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2497, \"end\": 2502, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999999899956, \"rank\": 1.0378449851270746e-11, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"everything\", \"from\": 2440, \"to\": 2450}, {\"ngram\": \"plan\", \"from\": 2459, \"to\": 2463}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 2465, \"to\": 2473}, {\"ngram\": \"a dip\", \"from\": 2484, \"to\": 2489}, {\"ngram\": \"the river\", \"from\": 2505, \"to\": 2514}, {\"ngram\": \"a century\", \"from\": 2552, \"to\": 2561}, {\"ngram\": \"high pollution levels\", \"from\": 2569, \"to\": 2590}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A little thing called the marquee opening ceremony will also take place along the river, rather than at the usual Olympic Stadium.\", \"from\": 2593, \"to\": 2723, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A little thing\", \"from\": 2593, \"to\": 2607}, {\"ngram\": \"the marquee opening ceremony\", \"from\": 2615, \"to\": 2643}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 2659, \"to\": 2664}, {\"ngram\": \"the river\", \"from\": 2671, \"to\": 2680}, {\"ngram\": \"the usual Olympic Stadium\", \"from\": 2697, \"to\": 2722}]}, {\"sentence\": \"France has spent 1.4billion euros to clean the river that runs through the heart of the capital and upgrade its creaky sewage systems for next Spring.\", \"from\": 2725, \"to\": 2875, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2725, \"end\": 2731, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.999999923332328, \"rank\": 7.611913096064946e-08, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrase